      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for CFD simulation must have documented version control, regression testing, and a traceable release process consistent with ASME V&V 40 MRL 3 requirements.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) is under version control with documented regression test suite. Release notes and issue tracking are maintained. Achieved level meets the required level for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must include method of manufactured solutions (MMS) or equivalent for the governing equations used in hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests were performed for the Navier-Stokes solver but MMS was not applied to the hemolysis transport sub-model. Achieved level falls one gradation below required, representing a known gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study with at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (3.2M, 8.1M, 18.4M cells) were generated with systematic refinement ratio ~1.35. Richardson extrapolation and GCI computed for hemolysis index; GCI < 4% on fine mesh. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented with uncertainty bounds on inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid properties.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental data provides flow rate and speed setpoints, but temperature-dependent viscosity uncertainty was not propagated. Fluid temperature varied ±2°C during testing; this was not reflected in boundary conditions. Achieved level is 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) computed between predicted and measured hemolysis index across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error of 11.3% across 5 operating points with validation uncertainty intervals reported. Comparison metric satisfies MRL 3 threshold. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly mappable to the clinical decision criterion (absolute hemolysis threshold).",
      "rationale": "NIH computed from both simulation and experiment using the same power-law damage model. Mapping to absolute clinical threshold is documented. QoI relevance is fully established for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on a geometry and operating envelope sufficiently representative of the COU device and conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry, which is a simplified surrogate. The actual VAD impeller geometry differs in blade count and clearance gap. Geometric similarity is partial; achieved level is 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, floating-point round-off, and time-integration error must each be bounded and reported.",
      "rationale": "Assessment of numerical solver error was considered beyond the scope of the current submission cycle. Residual convergence plots are available but formal bounding of iterative and round-off errors was deferred to a subsequent analysis phase. No requiredLevel or achievedLevel is assigned."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Potential for analyst-introduced error through incorrect setup, boundary condition misspecification, or post-processing mistakes must be evaluated via independent review or checklist.",
      "rationale": "A formal use-error review was not conducted within the project timeline. The simulation setup was performed by a single analyst without independent verification of boundary condition selections. This factor is flagged as beyond current scope without further justification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence closure and hemolysis damage model must be justified relative to the flow regime and stress history experienced by red blood cells in the VAD.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected; literature support for rotating machinery is documented. However, the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) is known to over-predict at low-shear conditions. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged but not fully bounded. Achieved level is 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (fluid properties, rotational speed, inlet flow conditions) must have documented sources and associated uncertainty estimates used in Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo sampling performed over blood viscosity (CV 8%), density (CV 1%), and inlet flow rate (CV 3%) distributions sourced from published hemocompatibility literature. Input uncertainty fully propagated to hemolysis index. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used for validation must be characterized for hematocrit, donor variability, and storage age; inter-sample variability must be reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental dataset reports mean hematocrit (40%) but does not disaggregate donor-to-donor variability or storage age effects on red blood cell fragility. Inter-sample uncertainty is not quantified. Achieved level is 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in the validation activity must be demonstrated to be equivalent (within stated tolerances) to those of the COU operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency mapping between FDA pump experimental inputs and COU VAD operating parameters was deferred as beyond current scope. Operating speed ranges partially overlap but no structured equivalency argument has been constructed."
